      "description": "This E92 M3 is a purist-spec example featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8 and a six-speed longitudinal manual gearbox. The naturally aspirated powerplant utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band peaking at an 8,400 RPM redline. The chassis remains exceptionally communicative, benefiting from an M-Variable helical limited-slip differential and a rigid subframe. This vehicle features the Electronic Damper Control (EDC) system for adjustable compression and rebound cycles, ensuring optimal contact patch management. While the exterior shows honest patina from spirited use, the mechanical vitals are robust, with recent attention paid to throttle actuators and fluid analysis. It is an mechanically sound, high-performance machine optimized for the enthusiast who values tactile steering feedback and atmospheric engine response.",
